channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: New Kamala Ads Are So Cringe, Some Think They're Actually for Trump
Battleground state rancher ‘outraged’ by Biden stopping wall construction as migrants pour into US
item.description: Arizona rancher Jim Chilton says he has had more than 3,500 migrants come across the border since the Biden administration took office and stopped wall construction.

item.title: Dems Concerned Middle East Could Cost Harris Votes
item.description: Democrats, who are already divided over the ongoing war between Israel and Hamas, are becoming more concerned the war has spread into more regional conflict will further separate the party and cost votes for Vice President Kamala Harris and in other down-ticket races.

item.title: Trump Brings Receipts Showing Crime Is Actually Way UP Under Kamala Harris
New poll indicates whether Harris or Trump is making gains with younger voters
item.description: A new poll indicates surging support among America's youngest voters for Vice President Kamala Harris in her 2024 showdown against former President Trump.

item.title: Oregon Removes Over 1,200 Voters for Failing to Prove U.S. Citizenship
item.description: Oregon elections officials said Monday they had struck over 1,200 people from the state's voter rolls after determining they did not provide proof of U.S. citizenship when they were registered to vote. Of those found to be possibly ineligible, only nine people voted in...

item.title: Team Kamala Tries to Look Like They're Oh So Into Football, Muff the Job Completely
Absentee voting kicks off in Missouri, North Carolina
item.description: Missouri and North Carolina began early voting on Tuesday, joining roughly 20 other states as the 2024 election kicks off.

item.title: Israel's Expanded Hezbollah Campaign Hits 1,300 Targets in Lebanon
item.description: Israeli airstrikes hit more than 1,300 targets in southern Lebanon as the military expanded its conflict against Hezbollah, Israeli Defense Forces said Monday. The strikes killed nearly 500 people and wounded more than 1,600, Lebanon’s Ministry of Public Health said.

item.title: Watch as Donald Trump Wins Hearts, and Probably a Few Votes, with Super Thoughtful Gesture
Fani Willis crisscrosses country fundraising with Democrat allies in DC, LA
item.description: Fulton County District Attorney Fani Willis traveled to Washington, D.C., Los Angeles and Texas to fundraise with Democratic allies for her re-election campaign.

item.title: Super PAC Supporting Hogan Places $18 Million Ad Buy
item.description: Larry Hogan, the former Maryland governor and Republican nominee for senator, is getting a major boost in his bid to win a senate seat in the deep blue state.

item.title: It's Hard To Be Hot: Beautiful People Are Complaining About How Hard They Have It
Piling on: A tsunami of anti-Trump pieces offer a stark contrast with Kamala’s upbeat coverage
item.description: Presidential candidates Donald Trump and Kamala Harris are running in the same election cycle, however, the coverage of each White House hopeful starkly contrasts.

item.title: Trump Encourages Christians, Gun Owners to Vote En Masse
item.description: As early voting has kicked off across the country, former President Donald Trump encouraged supporters in Pennsylvania on Monday night to vote, whether it's early, or through absentee ballot, or on Election Day.
